<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 4:54PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Rhea,
southwestern Bledsoe and northern Hamilton Counties through 630 PM
EDT/530 PM CDT/...
At 554 PM EDT/454 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 7 miles south of Pikeville, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dayton, Pikeville, Graysville, Brayton, Sale Creek and Palio.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
